comments: Curry (PHI) and Huerter (ATL) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Capela (ATL) cleanly blocks Embiid's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Bogdanovic (ATL) and Harris (PHI) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Bogdanovic (ATL) brings his right arm to Harris' (PHI) midsection and quickly releases as Harris receives the pass.
Bogdanovic (ATL) rests his right forearm on Harris' (PHI) side and marginal contact occurs at the end of Harris' drive.
Collins (ATL) establishes a legal guarding position in Harris' (PHI) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs at the end of the drive.
Young (ATL) is moving to the side of Korkmaz (PHI) and would avoid Korkmaz's right leg if he didn't extend it outside the plane of his body to initiate the marginal contact.

Harris (PHI) extends his right arm for the rebound when marginal contact occurs with Capela's (ATL) left wrist and head. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Simmons (PHI) brushes Young's (ATL) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Young dribbles in transition. Korkmaz (PHI) is turning away from Young when marginal contact occurs with Young's arm and front.
Embiid (PHI) makes contact to Young's (ATL) head during the follow-through of his driving shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Capela's (ATL) path and absorbs the contact.
Bogdanovic (ATL) grasps and then quickly releases Korkmaz's (PHI) shorts as the screen is set.
Korkmaz (PHI) sets the back screen on Bogdanovic (ATL) and gives Bogdanovic room to avoid the contact, which Korkmaz absorbs.
Capela (ATL) swipes forward and makes clean contact with the ball as simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Embiid's (PHI) side during the drive.

Collins (ATL) avoids making contact with Embiid (PHI) during his upward shooting motion and is whistled for the foul. However, Capela (ATL) initiates contact with Embiid's side during his upward shooting motion and affects his layup attempt.
Korkmaz (PHI) and Huerter (ATL) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Korkmaz (PHI) slightly extends his arms forward toward Young's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs with Young's front.
Embiid (PHI) applies a rested forearm to Collins' (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs as Collins drives toward the lane.
Harris (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive and incidental arm contact occurs with Collins (ATL) after he releases the pass.
Capela (ATL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Capela (ATL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Huerter (ATL) places his right hand to Curry's (PHI) right hip and quickly slides it off during the inbound.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Huerter's (ATL) path and absorbs the contact.
Capela (ATL) reaches forward to contest and Embiid (PHI) brings his arm into Capela's arm and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.

Simmons (PHI) and Collins (ATL) make incidental contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound. After communicating with the Replay Center, the call on the floor of ATL ball is confirmed.
Thybulle (PHI) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
Huerter (ATL) and Collins (ATL) each legally contest Curry's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
